<p>Stay open to your own evolution. The journey of faith is not a single decision but a direction&mdash;a persistent willingness to move toward truth wherever it leads. If something in these pages rang true, do not dismiss it. If something in your heart swelled when you read about the seed, about the burning on the road, about the thief who had nothing but honesty&mdash;that swelling is not random. Pay attention to it.</p>
<p>The invitation is simple: Come and see. Taste and see that the Lord is good (Psalm 34:8). Ask, and it shall be given you. Seek, and ye shall find. Knock, and it shall be opened unto you (Matthew 7:7). &ldquo;Behold, I stand at the door, and knock: if any man hear my voice, and open the door, I will come in to him&rdquo; (Revelation 3:20).</p>
<p>The door is yours to open. We pray that you will.</p>
